  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL)have had very poor humoral responses to
      pneumococcal polysaccharide vaccine (PPV). The vaccine in which pneumococcal polysaccharide
      antigens are conjugated to protein (PCV) have been immunogenic in CLL patients in our
      previous studies.

      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the duration of these vaccine-induced antibodies and
      the function of memory cells by giving a one dose of PPV-vaccine after several years of
      PCV-vaccination.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
